article.headline: Rice 80, SMU 40
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Michael Harris and Brock Gillespie scored 20 points each to lead Rice to an 80-40 win over Southern Methodist Tuesday night. Rice (12-4, 4-1 Western Athletic) led from the outset, jumping ahead 18-3 before SMU (8-8, 2-4) managed its first field goal with 14:10 remaining in the first half. Rice outshot the Mustangs 63 percent to 32 percent from the floor in the first half and led 44-25 at halftime. SMU made only 5-of-28 field goals in the second half for 18 percent to 50 percent shooting for Rice. Jason McKrieth added 13 points for Rice and J.R. Harrison had 11 points. Eric Castro led SMU with nine points.
